Brown meat in large stock pot. When meat is nearly cooked through add the onion and green pepper, and let cook for 5 minutes. Add diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, beef broth, cubed potatoes, cilantro and thyme. Season with salt and pepper and let simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Place 1/4 cup of rice on bottom of individual serving bowls. Pour soup over rice and garnish with grated Parmesan or Romano cheese.